01:52:51.150 --> 01:52:53.550
I thought it was
really interesting.

01:52:53.550 --> 01:52:56.550
Your plot is going
up quite steeply.

01:52:56.550 --> 01:52:59.690
When do we get-- so
we're like 2 million now.

01:52:59.690 --> 01:53:03.370
When do we get to 7.2 billion?

01:53:03.370 --> 01:53:05.660
-When the price drops.

01:53:05.660 --> 01:53:08.460
-That's meant seriously.

01:53:08.460 --> 01:53:11.030
-I don't think it's
going to anytime soon.

01:53:11.030 --> 01:53:13.150
I think there are huge
markets outside of the US.

01:53:13.150 --> 01:53:17.700
Most of the sales at the
moment are in the US or Canada.

01:53:17.700 --> 01:53:21.630
I think what's going to
drive that is utility.

01:53:21.630 --> 01:53:24.180
And the primary utility people
gain from the testing right

01:53:24.180 --> 01:53:25.520
now is genealogical.

01:53:25.520 --> 01:53:28.300
So they're finding second and
third cousins in the database.

01:53:28.300 --> 01:53:30.117
As the database
increases in size,

01:53:30.117 --> 01:53:31.200
you increase that utility.

01:53:31.200 --> 01:53:33.920
You're more likely to have
cousins that are in there.

01:53:33.920 --> 01:53:36.450
So it's price and utility.

01:53:36.450 --> 01:53:39.160
Sequencing is becoming
very, very cheap.

01:53:39.160 --> 01:53:41.190
And I'm on the
scientific advisory board

01:53:41.190 --> 01:53:44.850
of a startup called Helix,
which is a spin-off of Illumina.

01:53:44.850 --> 01:53:48.450
And one of the things that's
underpinning what they're doing

01:53:48.450 --> 01:53:51.160
is an exome-- so all
the coding regions

01:53:51.160 --> 01:53:54.680
of your genome-- for
significantly less than $100.

01:53:54.680 --> 01:53:57.230
And that is simply
unattainable outside

01:53:57.230 --> 01:53:59.700
of that organization right now.

01:53:59.700 --> 01:54:01.280
And as that price
approaches zero,

01:54:01.280 --> 01:54:04.530
it's going to become
much more widespread.

01:54:04.530 --> 01:54:10.560
-So once we have a
family tree of everybody,

01:54:10.560 --> 01:54:16.460
we've had instances where people
have been convicted or found

01:54:16.460 --> 01:54:19.760
based on getting DNA from their
brother or sister or something

01:54:19.760 --> 01:54:20.700
like that.

01:54:20.700 --> 01:54:24.700
So basically, it will
be nowhere to hide.

01:54:24.700 --> 01:54:26.220
-In essence, yeah.

01:54:26.220 --> 01:54:28.270
Yeah, that's what it means.

01:54:28.270 --> 01:54:31.710
I think, again, showing utility
is going to be important.

01:54:31.710 --> 01:54:33.510
But I do think that
in the next 10 years,

01:54:33.510 --> 01:54:36.130
it will be routine to
have your child tested

01:54:36.130 --> 01:54:41.160
either at birth or in utero with
non-invasive prenatal testing.

01:54:41.160 --> 01:54:43.600
And you will be seen
as an unfit parent

01:54:43.600 --> 01:54:45.580
if you choose to
ignore that information

01:54:45.580 --> 01:54:47.470
and not get yourself tested.

01:54:47.470 --> 01:54:51.230
And in fact, there was a lawsuit
a few years ago in France.

01:54:51.230 --> 01:54:55.130
A child born with Down syndrome
sued his parents successfully

01:54:55.130 --> 01:54:57.100
for having had him,
knowing that he was

01:54:57.100 --> 01:54:58.460
going to have Down Syndrome.

01:54:58.460 --> 01:55:00.376
Now, there was a technical
reason he did that.

01:55:00.376 --> 01:55:02.960
It was so he could access
certain financial benefits

01:55:02.960 --> 01:55:04.580
as a result of the ruling.

01:55:04.580 --> 01:55:07.612
But you have a couple
more lawsuits like that,

01:55:07.612 --> 01:55:09.820
and there's going to be a
strong incentive for people

01:55:09.820 --> 01:55:12.340
to do this testing.

01:55:12.340 --> 01:55:12.980
-Wow.

01:55:12.980 --> 01:55:13.730
