to come together,

02:01:35.920 --> 02:01:38.760
which is an amazing thing.

02:01:38.760 --> 02:01:41.650
What kinds of questions
do you see now

02:01:41.650 --> 02:01:45.720
as being really divisive
that DNA has yet

02:01:45.720 --> 02:01:47.290
to be able to answer?

02:01:47.290 --> 02:01:49.060
Maybe it could in the future.

02:01:49.060 --> 02:01:52.960
But what are some of those
big, dividing questions?

02:01:52.960 --> 02:01:55.400
And this could be to everyone.

02:01:55.400 --> 02:01:58.686
-I'll take it first, because
the other part of talk

02:01:58.686 --> 02:02:00.560
that I gave in Gibraltar
was this side-- what

02:02:00.560 --> 02:02:02.080
does the future look like?

02:02:02.080 --> 02:02:06.810
And from my point of view,
I'm interested in things

02:02:06.810 --> 02:02:10.510
like how did it come to be
that humans had this population

02:02:10.510 --> 02:02:12.200
structure in the past?

02:02:12.200 --> 02:02:14.700
What does that mean
relative to the way

02:02:14.700 --> 02:02:18.210
that we understand humans
to be distributed today

02:02:18.210 --> 02:02:21.210
as a widespread species with
great genetic commonalities

02:02:21.210 --> 02:02:22.830
among us?

02:02:22.830 --> 02:02:28.400
What can we make of rare
evidence in the past?

02:02:28.400 --> 02:02:30.010
I think of
archaeological evidence,

02:02:30.010 --> 02:02:31.880
and the fact that
we're now discovering

02:02:31.880 --> 02:02:36.409
that there's significant
plant use by Neanderthals.

02:02:36.409 --> 02:02:38.950
For instance, we used to think
of them as purely meat eaters,

02:02:38.950 --> 02:02:41.050
but we're finding the
evidence of the plant foods

02:02:41.050 --> 02:02:42.860
that they ate in
dental calculus.

02:02:42.860 --> 02:02:44.550
And now, we're
able to actually do

02:02:44.550 --> 02:02:48.480
some sequencing of oral
bacteria to try to understand

02:02:48.480 --> 02:02:50.220
their oral microbiomes.

02:02:50.220 --> 02:02:54.730
And those sorts of things
which suddenly give us

02:02:54.730 --> 02:02:57.690
a window on something that
we couldn't look at before,

02:02:57.690 --> 02:03:00.620
but the window is small,
and we know that it

02:03:00.620 --> 02:03:02.610
represents a larger world.

02:03:02.610 --> 02:03:06.370
How do we use rare evidence
to talk about things

02:03:06.370 --> 02:03:12.050
that were probably important,
but we can't see very much of?

02:03:12.050 --> 02:03:14.520
I don't know that
we're now polarized.

02:03:14.520 --> 02:03:16.350
I get a lot of happy feelings.

02:03:16.350 --> 02:03:18.870
I don't think that
we're divided by things.

02:03:18.870 --> 02:03:21.910
But I think that we're in a
phase where we haven't thought

02:03:21.910 --> 02:03:25.130
of the questions that
will dominate what we're

02:03:25.130 --> 02:03:26.797
doing for the next 15 years.

